      • create

        public static ConcatenateTable create(ExecutionMonitor mon,
                                      Optional<String> rowKeyDuplicateSuffix,
                                      boolean duplicatesPreCheck,
                                      BufferedDataTable... tables)
                               throws CanceledExecutionException
        Creates a new table from argument tables. This methods checks for row key duplicates over all given tables only if desired AND duplicate rows are not to be skipped and a duplicate suffix is not set.
        Parameters:
        mon - for progress info/cancellation
        rowKeyDuplicateSuffix - if set, the given suffix will be appended to row key duplicates.
        duplicatesPreCheck - if for duplicates should be checked BEFORE creating the result table. If false the row keys of the input tables MUST either be unique over all tables or a suffix appended.
        tables - Tables to put together.
        Returns:
        The new table.
        Throws:
        CanceledExecutionException - If cancelled.
        Since:
        3.1
